args: I hope Philia is okay. She seems down.
Yeah. I'm worried about her, too.\nShe's like that all the time lately.
I can't remember a day she's been normal\never since that fiend caught us off guard\nin the forest and we had to split up.
I wonder what the cause is, though?\nI've tried asking her, but she won't tell me.
Eh, folks can be sensitive sometimes.\nAll we can do is try and cheer her up.
I thought the same, which is why we're\nhere in the first place. I mean, she said\nshe wanted to come here, but...
Well, it doesn't seem to be having much of\nan effect. What should we do?
Say, Philia? Is there anywhere in\nparticular that you want to...
She's gone?! But she was just here!
We need to find her... Philia!\nWhere are you, Philia?!
(I thought I was going to see my prince,\nbut it turned out to be someone else...)
(But if we're really soul mates, how could\nsomething like that happen?)
Maybe the threads of fate holding us\ntogether aren't as strong as I thought?
...Oh no! I didn't mean to say that out loud.
If my prince hears me saying something\nlike that, he... Huh?
Huh?! Where am I?!\nWhere's my prince...and the others?!
I wasn't paying attention when I\nwas walking, so I don't even know\nwhere I am.
But if I go and try to find him and end up\nfinding someone else again instead...
Well, I'll just have to make him find ME!
I'll attach my handkerchief to an arrow,\nthen fire it up into the sky! ...Ha!
I wonder if he'll notice it?
...No! I'm SURE he'll notice!\nFate wants us to be together, after all.
I believe in you, my prince...
It's been so long. When is he going to\ncome for me?
It couldn't be that...that fate doesn't...
It's not him. Oh, I should have known.\nThis is just the WORST.
Hey, c'mon now! I ain't so bad.
Yer alone, right? Want me to give ya a\ntour of the town?
No, I do NOT! ...Save me, my prince!
Thank goodness I found you! We were all\nreally worried when you vanished!
Well, this was a big waste'a time. See ya.
My prince! You really came for me!
We really are bound together by fate!\nOtherwise, you wouldn't have noticed my\narrow like you did!
Though I only saw it for a moment,\nand I couldn't be confident it was yours.
Then why did you follow it?
As long as there was even the slightest\nchance it would lead me to you, that was\ngood enough.
...Of course! Hee hee. Of course.\nWhat have I been getting so worked\nup for all this time?
Even if fate isn't as absolute as I thought,\nthat's no reason to give up!
Um, I'm not sure what you're talking about,\nbut does this mean you're feeling better?
Then like I was asking earlier, is there\nanywhere in this town you want to look a—
Of course! And look, even if—and this is a\nBIG if—fate really isn't absolute...
It just means I have to try that much\nharder to pull us closer together!
Oh! Maybe we should skip looking at\nhalls and just do the ceremony today!
Oh, is today no good? Then when are you\nfree? Tomorrow? The weekend?
Uh... Umm... Actually, I just remembered\nI have something to do! Bye!
Waaaait! Come back, my darling prince!\nCome baaaack!
There's no point in trying to run away!\nFate will just keep pulling us together!
